#- ***********************Subgenii Ethno-morality
***********************
"Property is theft.[1]" -- P.J. Proudhon

"Property is liberty.[2]" -- P.J. Proudhon

"Property is impossible.[3]" -- P.J. Proudhon 
#- “Have some property to sell? I’m your guy!”- Bob

Proudhon, by piling up his contradictions this way, was not merely being French; he was trying to indicate that the abstraction "property" covers a variety of phenomena,
#- some pernicious and some beneficial.

"Property1 is theft" means that property1 created by the artificial laws of feudal, capitalist, and other authoritarian societies, is based on armed robbery. Companies like VALEX champion this method
#- of property acquisition and sell of the natural land for imaginary stock and then pawn it off on suckers, that is, when they aren’t exploiting New Friend labor.  

"Property2 is liberty" means that property2, that which will be voluntarily 
#- honored in a voluntary (anarchist) society, is the foundation of the liberty in that society.

"Property3 is impossible" means that property3 (=property1) creates so much conflict of interest that society society is in perpetual undeclared
#- civil war and must eventually devour itself (and properties 1 and 3 as well).

Whatever type of property you currently hold, we’d be happy to take it off your hands and flip it.
#- It is widely known in some small circles that Bob’s salesmanship is the primary factor in all real estate bubbles. How YOU acquire it is your own business.

-- Starting to get it?
